data.value: This app was created for controlling the Lego Mindstorms EV3 robot. The app was a part of a project work, which consisted of creating a prototype of an AGV for logistical work on a factory - following a predefined path, picking up an object and dropping it off. This GUI was developed by Polina Rymshina and Thao Pham, students of Fontys University of Applied Sciences, the Netherlands. The team consisted of 4 people, and two other team members - Djamali Dollison and Jharna Chhutari - have been working on creating an app for the robot in Lego Mindstorms IDE, defining the robot's movements.
